  "title": "Engineering Technician (West/5days/MNC)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Engineering Assistant / Technician (Industrialization)</strong></h2><p>📍 <strong>Location:</strong> West Region</p><h3><strong>About the Role</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a <strong>hands-on Engineering Assistant / Technician</strong> to support our <strong>Industrialization and New Product Introduction (NPI)</strong> activities. This role works closely with engineers to help bring new products from design into smooth, efficient manufacturing.</p><p>If you enjoy working on the production floor, documenting processes, and supporting new product builds, this role is for you.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Support Industrialization Engineers on <strong>new product introduction (NPI)</strong> and continuation projects</li><li>Assist in setting up and documenting <strong>production floor layouts</strong></li><li>Create <strong>Work Instructions (DWI)</strong> and <strong>process flow diagrams</strong></li><li>Collect and analyze basic <strong>manufacturing process data</strong></li><li>Support <strong>prototype and pilot builds</strong></li><li>Assist with <strong>process improvement and cost reduction</strong> initiatives</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to meet project goals</li><li>Communicate clearly with engineers, production teams, and stakeholders</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Diploma / ITE</strong> in Electrical, Electronics, or related engineering field</li><li><strong>Minimum 3 years’ experience</strong> in manufacturing or assembly environment</li><li>Familiar with <strong>manufacturing processes and documentation</strong></li><li>Basic problem-solving skills and attention to detail</li><li>Comfortable using <strong>Microsoft Office, Visio (or equivalent)</strong> and email</li><li>Organized, proactive, and able to work well with different teams</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits / Perks:</strong></p><ul><li>Hands-on experience in new product launches</li><li>Exposure to manufacturing engineering and industrialization</li></ul><p>📩 Apply now and grow your career!</p><p>(Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)<br /></p><p><strong>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte</strong> Ltd I EA License No.: 12C6285<br />Lee Pui Shan I Reg. No: R25157211<br /><strong>Email CV to : </strong><a href=\"mailto:jessicalee@envirodynamics.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>jessicalee@envirodynamics.com.sg</strong><br /><br /></a><strong>By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application</strong></p>",
